WEST NILE VIRUS - EURASIA (12): PORTUGAL, EQUINE, OIE
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Wed 27 Oct 2010
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2010; 23(43) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9879>


West Nile fever, Portugal
-------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 27 Oct 2010 from Dr Carlos Agrela
Pinheiro, [Delegate to OIE, Veterinary Services, Ministry of
Agriculture, Rural Development and Fisheries], Lisbon, Portugal

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 4 Oct 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 19 Oct 2010
Report date: 27 Oct 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 27 Oct 2010
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (01WNF/10) Palmela, Div Setubal, DSVR [Regional Veterinary
Directorate] of Lisbon and Tagus Valley
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Oct 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 1
Cases: 1
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 1
Slaughtered: 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors
Epidemiological comments: the animal was killed for animal welfare reasons.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; control of wildlife
reservoirs; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Research Laboratory
(national laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: IgG-capture ELISA
Test date: 19 Oct 2010
Result: positive

Species: Equidae
Test: IgM-capture ELISA
Test date: 19 Oct 2010
Result: positive

Species: Equidae
Test: real-time PCR
Test date: 19 Oct 2010
Result: negative

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In 2009, Austria, Hungary, Italy, and Spain reported West Nile Virus
infections in horses to the OIE WAHID database. This year (2010) we
are seeing equine disease in Spain, Morocco, and now Portugal. - Mod.PC]

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the map included in the
OIE report at the source URL above.
The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Portugal is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/0erI>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
